---
description: Hide Delete actions in kebab menus and require confirmation before destructive deletes.
alwaysApply: true
---

# Delete actions UX

All user-facing **Delete** actions must follow this pattern:

1. **Never** show a standalone Delete / Delete *entity* button in primary UI (card footers, page footers, toolbar rows).
2. Place Delete inside a **kebab (⋮) menu** using `src/components/KebabMenu.tsx` and existing `.kebab-*` styles.
3. **Always** require confirmation before deleting. Danger kebab items must set `danger: true` and a required `confirmMessage` (enforced by `KebabMenu` typings).
4. Use the **in-app** confirm sheet (`ConfirmSheet` via `KebabMenu`) — never `window.confirm` for deletes (native dialogs are unreliable in this PWA).
5. Confirmation copy must follow: `Are you sure you want to delete [x]? This can't be undone.` — name the specific item (and cascade impact when relevant).

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — visible delete button / native confirm
<button className="btn btn-danger" onClick={() => {
  if (confirm('Delete?')) void deleteThing()
}}>Delete</button>

// ✅ GOOD — kebab + in-app confirm
<KebabMenu
  aria-label="Thing actions"
  items={[
    {
      label: 'Delete',
      danger: true,
      confirmMessage: `Are you sure you want to delete "${thing.name}"? This can't be undone.`,
      onSelect: () => void deleteThing(),
    },
  ]}
/>
```

Applies to new screens and when editing existing delete UI.
